			<link>http://jlleblanc.com/articles/41-podcast-suite-version-11-stable</link>
			<guid>http://jlleblanc.com/articles/41-podcast-suite-version-11-stable</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: left;">Podcast Suite version 1.1 stable is now available for download: <a href="http://jlleblanc.com/com_podcast_v1.1.zip">component</a>, <a href="http://jlleblanc.com/mod_podcast_v.1.1.zip">module</a>, <a href="http://jlleblanc.com/bot_podcast_v1.1.zip">plugin</a>. This is mainly a bug fix release, with the following issues resolved:<br /><br /></div><div style="text-align: left;"><ul><li>Added support for &lt;itunes:author&gt;</li><li>Fixed the iTunes category format</li><li>Fixed player autostart issues in IE</li><li>Fixed the issue where RSS feeds were downloading instead of displaying in the browser</li><li>Enclosures can now appear in both the introtext and fulltext</li><li>Off-site links now work properly</li><li>Fixed so that filenames with parenthesis are properly handled <br /></li></ul>The following features were also added:<br /><ul><li>The module can now display pcast:// links for one-click subscriptions, as well as display an additional link to the actual feed</li><li>Quicktime is now supported for AAC playback</li><li>Category pre-selects have been added for iTunes</li><li>Feeds for separate Joomla categories are now available.</li></ul>Uninstall the old versions of all three, then reinstall the new copies.<br /></div><br /><br />

Translations:<br />
<a href="http://www.nik-o-mat.de/joomlafan/joomla-software/podcastsuite-1.1-stable---deutsch.html">German</a><br />
<br /><br />


webman911 has graciously written a <a href="http://forum.joomla.org/index.php/topic,138839.0.html">step-by-step tutorial</a> for using the podcasting suite!]]></description>
